{
  "analysis": "I'm getting fragments of the disassembly but need a more systematic approach. The main function is large (~0x14F0 bytes). I should dump it to a file and examine it in controlled chunks. The key challenge is understanding the ray tracing algorithm: camera setup, ray generation, sphere intersection, sky/terrain coloring, and noise generation for terrain.",
  "plan": "Get the complete function list in the user code range, disassemble all helper functions, and use `grep` to find key instructions (calls, constants, branches) in the main disassembly. This will help me understand the overall structure without reading every instruction.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "nm /app/mystery | awk '$1>=\"0000000000401000\" && $1<=\"0000000000403100\" {print}' | grep -E ' (t|T) '\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "objdump -d --start-address=0x4020a0 --stop-address=0x4021a0 /app/mystery\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep -n 'call' /tmp/main.dis | head -60\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep -nE '(movss|mulss|addss|subss|divss|sqrtss|comiss|cvttss2si)' /tmp/main.dis | grep -E '0x48|0x40' | head -80\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep -n 'call' /tmp/helpers.dis | head -40\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
